The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, May 5: The rate of inflation fell marginally to 3.54 per cent for the week ended April 22 from 3.55 per cent in the previous week despite higher prices of eggs and wheat. The rate of inflation was also much lower than 5.96 per cent in the year-ago period, according to the data released by the government. The wholesale price index (WPI) was up 0.2 per cent to 198.8 points from 198.5 points a year ago.

 Mumbai, May 5: The forex reserves increased by $3.4 billion to $160.677 billion during the week ended April 28, from $157.262 billion during the week ended April 21. 

 Mumbai, May 5: Cipla Ltd has allotted 46.63 crore bonus shares in the ratio of 2:3. The company?s board had allotted the bonus shares of Rs 2 each aggregating to Rs 93.27 crore in the proportion of three equity shares for every two held.

 New Delhi, May 5: A group of secretaries will meet to decide the next course of action regarding Bharat Aluminium Company (Balco). The mines ministry has decided not to sell the government?s remaining stake in the company.

 Mumbai, May 5: ABG Heavy Industries has entered into an agreement with Korea-based Doosan Heavy Industries and Construction Company Ltd for projects in India and other Asian countries.




